<p class=story>The Center for Connected Health in Boston reported in a study that text messaging improved treatment adherence and self-care for dermatology patients suffering from atopic dermatitis19. In the study, 25 patients received daily text messages over a period of six weeks. The text messages included treatment reminders and educational content pertaining to their health condition. At the end of the six week study, patients reported and improvement of treatment adherence of 72% and roughly 68% of the patients reported an improvement in self-care behaviors to help their conditions. 
</p>

